Invocat  
=======
A nondeterministic, probabilistic programming language by C & M Antoun.  
2015-03-18  


Contents
--------
invocat.lua   -- The Invocat lexer, parser, and interpreter.  
README        -- This file  

test/                 -- Contains a small test suite and sample programs  
    the-whale.inv     -- Markov example trained on some of Moby Dick  
    tests.inv         -- Example program  

misc/
    train-markov.lua  -- Convert an input file to an Invocat Markov chain  
    the-whale.txt     -- Text file used to generate the-whale.inv


Usage
-----
Invocat is built in Lua and requires a Lua interpreter. If a file name argument
is provided, the file will be executed as an Invocat program. With no arguments,
Invocat will read from standard input.

    $ ./invocat.lua [file]

To run the Markov text generation example:

    $ ./invocat.lua test/the-whale.inv

The output from the Markov trainer can be piped directly to Invocat.

    $ ./misc/train-markov.lua [file] | ./invocat

